  "text": "Γ it has been parameterized in an ad hoc manner in several papers following the first ones surveyed by [CITATION_1] . The aim of this note is to find its explicit form, which amounts to find the explicit form for λ d it . The Lagrange multiplier related to a quantitative constraint is generally an increasing function of the gap between the \"notional\" denoted I UC it and the \"constrained\" control variable (investment for the firm facing credit rationing) denoted I C it . The expression γ t + λ d it is given by the marginal condition on investment in the credit rationing regime:",
